arch:property.oc:show_val: Medium-size unit with range of taxa and fragment sizes. Much is burnt. All is quite friable: millions of modern breaks! Some antler and horn core, both burnt and unburnt. Many sheep metapodials and phalanges, all burnt except for 1 second phalanx. Unburnt bone uniform light brown. Sample 137 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, only diagnostics recorded, rest as flot frags. Largish sample, mostly small fragments of sheep-size and large mammal scrap, with some up to 4 cm. Several phalanges, bits of metapodia. Fair amount of burning, low and high temperature. Not much weathering, a little digestion. Last number = 127
